Description: AXYS Analytical Services provides commercial laboratory focused on organic contaminant measurement in all matrices for multiple industries.
Full Description: AXYS has come a long way since spring 1974 when we began benchmarking contaminants in Canada’s Arctic ahead of oil and gas development. In the last forty years we’ve evolved into North America’s leading commercial laboratory focused on organic contaminant measurement in all matrices for multiple industries and governments around the world. Our success is largely due to the partnership with our clients and their relentless pursuit of understanding environmental impacts founded on scientific rigour, technical expertise and highest integrity data. You’ve demanded excellence and exhorted us to stretch to meet your needs.  Along the way, we’ve innovated and found better ways to support scientifically defensible presentation of key and emerging issues – PCBs in mothers’ milk, naphthenic acids in Oil Sands waters, pharmaceuticals in waste water effluent and more. Analytical leadership requires scientific excellence and specialized expertise. AXYS focuses on the analysis of emerging organic contaminants using advanced gas and liquid chromatographic techniques, linked with single and tandem mass spectroscopy. We precisely characterize and measure the chemical contaminants in samples as varied as human blood, fish tissue, water and sediments. Our ability to detect extremely low concentrations of organic chemicals, in small sample sizes and complex and matrices, is unmatched by conventional, general service, environmental laboratories. Industry leading ultra-trace analysis and multi-matrix combined extraction techniques, paired with exceptional client supporting chemical interpretation, delivers true “analytical advantage” to our clients: The leading lab and most precise data to best inform your decisions.

Description: A convenient single-serve, portable, pour-over coffee manufacturer, that is specialized in coffee filter and package technology.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: [Caffe Borsa Corporate Profile] Founded by two passionate coffee and tea connoisseurs who were frustrated that they could not find an easy way to get their cups to taste like the extraordinarily deep-bodied but clear-tasting drip coffee they drank at the specialty coffee houses, Caffe Borsa has introduced a new delivery system, Hand Drip, as the first of its kind, providing a pour over specialty coffee experience that offers single service convenience with a palate-pleasing flavor - all without using a machine. Caffe Borsa believes that coffee should be enjoyed without boundaries: outside, inside, at work, on travel, with friends, or alone in peace. The magic of Caffe Borsa’s delivery system is brewing it yourself, whenever you wish, wherever you may be – with just hot water. In today’s fast paced technological world, why should we have to worry about whether we will have our favorite coffee to depend on? Caffe Borsa places an importance on conserving the planet’s natural resources and making the future a better place. We’ve developed a product that doesn’t require a machine and the product is made of 100% Arabica ground coffee and special filter paper only. Even the coffee is air-tight packed in single serving proportions, so no unused ground beans are wasted.  The management team at Caffe Borsa includes decades of combined experience in food and drink product development, sales, and marketing. Scott Choi comes from a background of international trade and marketing. Jim Song, once an engineer and now an entrepreneur, brings his technical expertise and financial management experience to the table. Paul Tuan and Eric Li also bring cash flow management and debt-financing expertise from working at the investment banks.  Their advisor Joe Di Stanislao, past president of the National Specialty Food Broker Association, demonstrates his understanding of the marketplace with his over 40 years of serving as a broker in the industry. Food service advisor, Bill Waldo, past president of Supreme Foodservice, Inc, has over 20 years of experience in food service sales and marketing to hotels, restaurants, and distributors. Based in Irvine, CA, Caffe Borsa works with coffee traders and tea farmers to deliver top-quality products from dedicated growers to end users who appreciate high quality and exquisite taste. Caffe Borsa has established strong relationships with distributors, freight forwarders, custom brokers, the Food and Drug Administration, and Customs and Border Protection.
Industry Groups: Food and Beverage, Transportation, Travel and Tourism
